<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-11-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-11-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="483" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d483">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/385.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-29"><hi rend="italic">November 29, 1910</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 152.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department acknowledges the receipt of
                            your dispatch 241 of the 10th instant, in which you report at length
                            regarding the recent anti-American riots in Mexico City. You also
                            outline the action taken by you toward bringing these unfortunate
                            circumstances to an end, and the satisfactory results of such action.
                            Your course in the matter, as outlined in the dispatch, is approved by
                            the Department.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>